Title : Siamang putih
Text : {{Orphan|date=October 2015}}

'''''Siamang putih''''' is the name of an [[Indonesia]]n [[folklore|folk legend]].<ref name="Navis">
{{cite book
  |first=A.A.|last=Navis
  |year=2001
  |title=Seri Pendidikan Budaya: Cerita Rakyat dari Sumatera
  |trans-title=Cultural Education Series: Folklore of Western Sumatra
  |volume=3
  |location=Jakarta|publisher=Grasindo
}}</ref><ref name="Ananda">
{{cite book
  |first=Sheina|last=Ananda
  |year=2013
  |title=Rangkuman 100 cerita rakyat Indonesia dari Sabang sampai Merauke
  |trans-title=One Hundred Folk Tales of Indonesia from Sabang to Merauke
  |location=Jakarta|publisher=Anakkita
}}</ref>  In this legend, a princess promises that she will wait for her fianc√©. After years of waiting for his return, she breaks her promise and is cursed to live out her live as a white [[siamang]] (an Indonesian ape).<ref name="Navis"/> This folktale is also known from the Malay Peninsula, where siamangs occur as well.<ref name="Skeat">
